<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8405633>
    dc:description "Fig. 45. Conasprella (Fusiconus) coriolisi (R̂ckel, Richard & Moolenbeek, 1995). A. Holotype, Coral Sea, Capel Bank, Lord Howe Rise, 240 m depth, 41.5 mm (MNHN-IM-2000-2570). B. Coral Sea, Kelso Bank, 225‒230 m depth, 40.0 mm. C. Off New Caledonia, 378‒414 m depth, 39.8 mm. D. S New Caledonia, 225‒230 m depth, 47.8 mm. E. Coral Sea, Nova Bank, 330 m depth, 56.0 mm. F. Coral Sea, Capel Bank, 150‒225 m depth, 37.8 mm. G. Coral Sea, W Bellona, 356‒438 m depth, 46.5 mm. H. Coral Sea, Nova Bank, 305 m depth, 49.2 mm. I. Off New Caledonia, 300‒302 m depth, 39.0 mm. J. E New Caledonia, 250 m depth, 47.0 mm. K. Same collection data as for specimen J, 21.5 mm. L. Protoconch of specimen from the Coral Sea, Argo Bank, 272 m depth. M. Radular tooth of specimen C from off New Caledonia, 378‒414 m depth, 39.8 mm. Scale bars = 10 mm, unless otherwise stated." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8405633/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

